news.title: NGT restrains Oberoi Realty from creating third-party rights in Worli project
news.para: It has ordered the Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA), the State Environment Impact Assessment Authority (SEIAA) Maharashtra and the Maharashtra Pollution Control Board (MPCB) to hold a joint meeting within a month to ensure compliance with the project.

news.title: SC refuses to reopen settlement of home buyers and Supertech on refund
news.para: It said that in cases where home loans are outstanding, Supertech shall clear the home loans on or before March 31 and furnish NOCs from the concerned financial institutions to the home buyers, no later than within a period of April 10, 2022.

news.title: Birla Corporation's net profit slips 59.27% to Rs 60.45 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Birla Corporation's revenue from operation was down 1.49 per cent to Rs 1,750.06 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 1,776.62 crore.

news.title: Godrej Properties calls off DB Realty deal
news.para: On Thursday, Godrej Properties had announced that it would invest Rs 400 crore to acquire around 10 per cent stake in DB Realty and another Rs 300 crore to set up a joint platform for undertaking slum redevelopment project.

news.title: HeidelbergCement CEO optimistic for 2022, flags new CO2 roadmap
news.para: Dominik von Achten, who has led the world's second-largest cement maker for two years, said strong preliminary results for 2021 provided the basis for continued growth in 2022 or "perhaps even accelerate it a little".

news.title: Apartment registrations in Kolkata decline by 33% year-on-year in January 2022
news.para: At 2,391 units, the January 2022 apartment registrations declined by 33% YoY over January 2021, said Knight Frank India, the leading real estate consultancy.

news.title: Evergrande to push ahead with sale of Hong Kong land after receiver appointment: Source
news.para: U.S. asset manager Oaktree Capital Management, a lender to Evergrande to develop a vast land plot in the rural Yuen Long district, has sought to seize control of the asset by appointing a receiver, a separate person said last month.

news.title: Shree Cement's net profit dips 24% to Rs 482.70 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Shree Cement's net consolidated income stood at Rs 3,750.9 crore in Q3 FY22, a growth of 2 per cent from Rs 3,664.72 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kolkata: East-West Metro gets Rs 1,100 crore funds boost in 2022-23
news.para: For people of the city, from where the country’s first Metro had chugged out 38 years ago, zipping through Sector V-Howrah Maidan in 27 minutes flat will certainly be a fairytale.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace Developers posts Rs 24.86 crore profit in Q3 FY22
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers net consolidated total income stood at Rs 33.32 crore in Q3 FY22, a dip of from Rs 70.19 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Telangana HC stay mining operations of Deccan Cements
news.para: Telangana HC has stayed mining activity of Deccan Cements in one of its mines in Surypet district till next date of hearing.On Wednesday, the HC heard the petition filed by environmental activist Koteshwar Rao against Deccan Cements.

news.title: DB Realty deal overhang for Godrej Properties in short term
news.para: DB Realty, which already has partnered with Bangalore-based Prestige Estates for some larger projects in JV format, saw its shares hitting 5 per cent upper circuit limit at Rs 100.90. Godrej Industries shares, on the other hand, were down 10 per cent intraday

news.title: Swachh survey: Ludhiana won't meet construction & demolition waste criteria
news.para: A project on processing plant is in progress under Smart City Mission, but is nowhere near complete. However, the officials said they are unable to think about anything else except for solid waste which is a major issue.

news.title: CBI books Amrapali Smart City Developers, its directors for bank fraud of over Rs 472 crore
news.para: The company has allegedly caused a loss of Rs 472.24 crore to a consortium of banks comprising the erstwhile Corporation Bank (now the Union Bank of India), the Oriental Bank of Commerce (now the Punjab National Bank) and the Union Bank of India.

news.title: Strict FSI norms for land owners rolled out in Secunderabad Cantonment
news.para: The most important guideline: only one parking floor in the form of cellar or basement or stilt floor at a height not exceeding 2.75 meters.
